### Area

core

### Describe the bug

According to the [documentation](https://www.keycloak.org/docs-api/latest/javadocs/org/keycloak/models/utils/KeycloakModelUtils.html#findUserByNameOrEmail(org.keycloak.models.KeycloakSession,org.keycloak.models.RealmModel,java.lang.String)) `org.keycloak.models.utils.KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail(KeycloakSession session, RealmModel realm, String username)` accepts a "username or email of user" and returns the corresponding `UserModel` if such user exists. 
In newer releases (version > 0.32) of the [keycloak-magiclink](https://github.com/p2-inc/keycloak-magic-link) extension the usage of this function has been introduced and I have observed the following behaviour:
Relevant code snippet (note: the log statements are not part of the Github codebase, I added them manully for testing purposes):
```
log.debugf("getOrCreate() - Pass email '%s' to KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail()", email);
UserModel user = KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail(session, realm, email);
if (user == null) {
  log.debugf("getOrCreate() - Returned user is null!");
}
else {
  log.debugf("getOrCreate() - Returned user has email '%s'", user.getEmail());
}
```
The value of "email" is correctly determined by calling `AuthenticationFlowContext.getUser().getEmail()` from the `AuthenticationFlowContext` object provided to the authenticator's `challenge(AuthenticationFlowContext context, FormMessage errorMessage)` method.
The log output for a valid value (i.e. email address of an existing Keycloak user in that realm) of "email" in our testing environment is:
```
[io.phasetwo.keycloak.magic.MagicLink] (executor-thread-1) getOrCreate() - Pass email '<CORRECT_EMAIL_BLANKED>' to KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail()
[io.phasetwo.keycloak.magic.MagicLink] (executor-thread-1) getOrCreate() - Returned user is null!
```
**EDIT (updated problem analysis)**
This is the current implementation of `KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail(...)`:
```
public static UserModel findUserByNameOrEmail(KeycloakSession session, RealmModel realm, String username) {
    if (realm.isLoginWithEmailAllowed() && username.indexOf('@') != -1) {
        UserModel user = session.users().getUserByEmail(realm, username);
        if (user != null) {
            return user;
         }
     }

     return session.users().getUserByUsername(realm, username);
}
```
Due to the condition `realm.isLoginWithEmailAllowed()` this will never work when an email address is supplied for a realm which does not actually use the email address as alternative to the username (like it is the case in our environment).

So I think the solution would be to either remove `realm.isLoginWithEmailAllowed()` from above condition or to make it more clear in the documentation that an email address as argument will only work if the realm allows login with the email address 
instead of the username (currently Javadoc only says: "Try to find user by username or email for authentication" and "@param username username or email of user" which does not make you aware of this restriction without having a look at the source code directly). Would it introduce drawbacks if this condition would be removed?

### Version

26.1.3

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

`org.keycloak.models.utils.KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail(KeycloakSession session, RealmModel realm, String username)` should return the corresponding `UserModel` when the email address of an existing user is supplied as value for "username" (for a realm with settings: "Email as username" disabled and "Login with email" disabled)

### Actual behavior

`org.keycloak.models.utils.KeycloakModelUtils.findUserByNameOrEmail(KeycloakSession session, RealmModel realm, String username)` returns `null` when the email address of an existing user is supplied as value for "username" (for a realm with settings: "Email as username" disabled and "Login with email" disabled)

### How to Reproduce?

I tested this using the keycloak-magiclink extension (possibly there is an easier approach to test this function in isolation?) 
- have a Keycloak realm with at least one user where the username differs from the email address (realm settings: "Email as username" disabled and "Login with email" disabled)
- have an authentication flow including the "Email OTP" authenticator from keycloak-magiclink as described in the [Readme](https://github.com/p2-inc/keycloak-magic-link)
- try to login with the username and the mail including the email OTP never arrives, because the email address is not resolved to a Keycloak user

### Anything else?

Please let me know if further information would be required.

